cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the development of an infinitary logic with linear-algebraic operators and its expressive power. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of graph properties and their definability in certain logics. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper involves the study of graph isomorphism and its approximations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves the study of graph properties and their computational complexity. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves the study of graph isomorphism and its approximations, which can be relevant in game theory.
